=== sw-cor24-rpg-ii Minimal RPG-II Demo (Reverse + Gate-Off Variant) ===
Program:
H  control header
F  input file INFIL
I  field 01: A0110  (10-char input slice)
I  field 02: A0810  (3-char input tail slice)
C  REVR01 -> calc work field
O  DETAIL01 output (10 chars) gated when indicator 01 is off
O  DETAIL02 output (3 chars)

Current boundary:
- Real today: output gating now supports two tiny parsed conditions:
  gate 01 requires indicator 01 on, and gate 02 requires indicator 01 off.
- This variant composes REVR01 with gate 02, so the reversed 10-byte field
  emits only because REVR01 leaves indicator 01 cleared.

Current runtime-produced output:
A10 DROCER
B20 DROCER
C30 DROCER

Authored source: rpg2.hlasm
Tiny demo source: tiny_rpg_demo_revr_gateoff.src
Generated source: build/rpg2.generated.s
